comments: Beverley (LAL) makes clean contact with the ball and cleanly dislodges it away from Bogdanovic (DET) prior to incidental arm contact occurring.
Burks (DET) engages with James (LAL) off ball and marginal body contact occurs as James (LAL) gathers the post entry pass.
Ivey (DET) makes clean contact with the ball and cleanly dislodges it away from James (LAL) prior to incidental arm contact occurring.
Duren (DET) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Duren (DET) slightly extends his arm toward Davis' (LAL) off ball and marginal contact occurs as they both pursue the loose ball.
Bey (DET) places his forearm to Davis' (LAL) front off ball and deflects the entry pass before incidental contact occurs.
Beverley (LAL) lightly brushes Ivey's (DET) hand while contesting his driving shot attempt.
Davis (LAL) engages with Duren (DET) off-ball and marginal contact occurs as Davis (LAL) releases away to retrieve the pass.
Bogdanovic (DET) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Reaves (LAL) and Burks (DET) mutually engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
James (LAL) swipes down and deflects the ball out-of-bounds during Burks' (DET) dribble.
James (LAL) maintains a legal guarding position and cleanly dislodges the ball away from Burks (DET).
Ivey (DET) establishes himself in Schroder's (LAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Burks (DET) hands off the ball in Schroder's (LAL) path and absorbs the contact.
Burks (DET) engages with Schroder (LAL) off-ball and marginal contact occurs as Burks (DET) releases away to retrieve the pass.
Davis (LAL) moves alongside Burks's (DET) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Burks (DET) jumps along Schroder's (LAL) path and marginal lower body contact occurs as Schroder (LAL) extends his leg out during his driving shot attempt.
Schroder (LAL) brings his off-arm outward and marginal contact occurs with Burks (DET) during the driving shot attempt.
Davis (LAL) maintains legal guarding position while defending Ivey's (DET) drive to the basket.
Beverley (LAL) contests the jump shot attempt and avoids making contact with Bogdanovic's (DET) arm.
James (LAL) and Duren (DET) mutually engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Duren (DET) extends his arms against Davis' (LAL) body in the lane and the contact affects his ability to retrieve the loose ball.
Ivey (DET) makes clean contact with the ball and deflects it away from James (LAL) prior to incidental contact occurring.
Schroder (LAL) maintains his arms within the frame of his body and does not deliver illegal contact to Bey (DET) during the screen.
Bey (DET) and James (LAL) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs prior to the entry pass.
Davis (LAL) brings his hands toward Bey (DET) and marginal contact occurs as Davis (LAL) releases away to roll.
Ivey (DET) brings his arm toward James's (LAL) front and marginal contact occurs during James's (LAL) drive.
Davis (LAL) is in the lane for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Bey (DET) contests the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Reaves's (LAL) arm after the release.
Beverley (LAL) defends Bogdanovic (DET) off-ball and briefly places his resting hands against Bogdanovic's (DET) body before correcting.
Schroder (LAL) places a stayed hand against Burks' (DET) body during his upward shooting motion and does not apply force defending his jump shot attempt.
Duren (DET) and Davis (LAL) mutually engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Bey (DET) initiates contact with Davis's (LAL) arm and affects Davis's (LAL) SQBR.
